{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Prepare-and-plan","level":4,"type":"heading","text":"Prepare and plan"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Turn on lights, open all doors and closets, open window treatments so the window corners are visible, and clear your planned path of people, pets, and objects. Clean your camera lens."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"ico_howToScan_rightRoom.png"}]},{"anchor":"Start-in-a-corner","level":4,"type":"heading","text":"Start in a corner"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Point camera at the floor, furniture, or other details — not a blank wall."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"ico_howToScan_corner.png"}]},{"anchor":"Scan-like-youre-painting-a-fence","level":4,"type":"heading","text":"Scan like you’re painting a fence"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Start from the floor, sweep up the wall, move to the side, and then back down, and repeat this pattern. Scan around blank walls, mirrors, and reflective surfaces."}]},{"anchor":"Stay-within-3-10-feet-of-the-walls","level":4,"type":"heading","text":"Stay within 3-10 feet of the walls"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The maximum LiDAR range is 15 feet, but 3-10 feet will yield the best accuracy. Step backward or forward to keep details such as edges, colors, architectural details, furniture, or wall art in view. Try to avoid blank walls."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"ico_howToScan_feet.png"}]},{"anchor":"Move-in-a-single-continuous-loop","level":4,"type":"heading","text":"Move in a single, continuous loop"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Avoid zig-zagging and re-scanning the same area repeatedly. Brief overlap is not a problem and expected."}]},{"anchor":"Try-a-U-pattern-in-tight-spaces","level":4,"type":"heading","text":"Try a U-pattern in tight spaces"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tight spaces can require a different approach. Try a U-pattern when you can’t stay 3 feet away from walls, like with hallways, kitchen islands, stairs, or closets."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"ico_howToScan_uPattern.png"}]},{"anchor":"Scanning-an-entire-house","level":4,"type":"heading","text":"Scanning an entire house"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Scan room by room, several rooms at once, or up to a whole floor in a single scan. If you break it up, make sure scans share a common area. Scan the staircases or exteriors separately."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"ico_howToScan_allowedObjects"}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/canvassdk\/howtoscan"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.occipital.CanvasSDK\/documentation\/CanvasSDK\/HowToScan","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"How to Scan","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"CanvasSDK"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.occipital.CanvasSDK\/documentation\/CanvasSDK"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Scanner","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.occipital.CanvasSDK\/documentation\/CanvasSDK\/CanvasScanner","doc:\/\/com.occipital.CanvasSDK\/documentation\/CanvasSDK\/CanvasScannerDelegate","doc:\/\/com.occipital.CanvasSDK\/documentation\/CanvasSDK\/CanvasScanner\/Error"],"generated":true}],"references":{"ico_howToScan_feet.png":{"alt":"scan-feet","type":"image","identifier":"ico_howToScan_feet.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/ico_howToScan_feet.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://com.occipital.CanvasSDK/documentation/CanvasSDK/CanvasScanner":{"role":"symbol","title":"CanvasScanner","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"te